.TH BUDDYDRIVE "1" "April 2025" "Unknown option: version" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
buddydrive \- P2P encrypted folder sync for you and your buddies
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B buddydrive
\fI\,<command> \/\fR[\fI\,options\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
BuddyDrive is a peer-to-peer encrypted folder synchronization tool that lets you sync folders with friends across the internet, bypassing NATs and firewalls. No cloud. No middleman. Just peer-to-peer encrypted sync.
.PP
BuddyDrive consists of three main components:
.TP
.B buddydrive
The command-line interface and sync daemon. This is the core component that handles folder synchronization, peer discovery via DHT, NAT traversal, and end-to-end encryption using XChaCha20-Poly1305.
.TP
.B buddydrive-gui
A GTK4 desktop application for monitoring and configuration. Provides a graphical interface to view sync status, manage folders and buddies, and configure settings.
.PP
